; Regression test for issue #560: Getting balances of parent and empty/zero accounts
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/560
;
; When a parent account had multiple visited children but only one displayable
; (non-zero) child, the balance report omitted the parent header, making it
; look as if the zero-balance siblings had never been posted to. The fix in
; src/output.cc treats a parent with multiple visited children as worth
; displaying even when only one child has a non-zero balance, consistent with
; the existing behavior when two or more children are displayable.

2024/01/01 Opening Balance
    Assets:Bank:Checking    $100.00
    Equity:Opening          $-100.00

2024/01/02 Transfer to Savings
    Assets:Bank:Savings     $100.00
    Assets:Bank:Checking    $-100.00

; Parent Assets:Bank should appear because both Checking and Savings were
; posted to, even though Checking zeroed out.
test bal Assets:Bank
             $100.00  Assets:Bank
             $100.00    Savings
--------------------
             $100.00
end test

; With --empty, the parent header and zero-balance child are both shown.
test bal Assets:Bank --empty
             $100.00  Assets:Bank
               $0.00    Checking
             $100.00    Savings
--------------------
             $100.00
end test

; A parent with a single visited child and no other siblings still collapses
; to a single leaf line (single-path collapse is the intended design).
test bal Equity
            $-100.00  Equity:Opening
end test
